        By
        <span><a href="/person/r/john-roberts">John Roberts</a>, <!----></span><span><a href="/person/p/alex-pappas">Alex Pappas</a><!----><span class="article-source"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.foxnews.com/"> | Fox News</a></span></span></span><!----></div><div class="article-social"><div class="social-icons"><ul><li class="fb"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a></li><li class="tw"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Twitter</a></li><li class="flipboard"><a rel="nofollow">Flipboard</a></li><li class="comments"><a href="#" rel="nofollow"><span>Comments</span></a></li><li class="print"><a href="/politics/trump-offers-heather-nauert-un-ambassador-job-source-says.print" rel="nofollow">Print</a></li><li class="email"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Email</a></li></ul></div></div></div></header><div class="article-content-wrap sticky-columns"><div class="article-content"><div class="article-body"><div class="featured featured-video video-ct" data-v-275a95fe><div class="contain" data-v-275a95fe><div class="control" data-v-275a95fe><a href="#" class="top" data-v-275a95fe></a><a href="#" class="close" data-v-275a95fe>close</a></div><div class="video-container" data-v-275a95fe><div data-widget-type="embed" data-video-id="5771224771001" data-video-domain="foxnews" class="m video-player" data-v-275a95fe><a href="http://video.foxnews.com/v/5771224771001" data-v-275a95fe><img src="https://a57.foxnews.com/media2.foxnews.com/BrightCove/694940094001/2018/04/16/931/524/694940094001_5771227138001_5771224771001-vs.jpg?ve=1&amp;tl=1" alt="Heather Nauert: US is in Syria to defeat ISIS" data-v-275a95fe><span class="overlay" data-v-275a95fe>Video</span></a></div></div><div class="info" data-v-275a95fe><div class="caption" data-v-275a95fe><h4 class="title" data-v-275a95fe><a href="http://video.foxnews.com/v/5771224771001" data-v-275a95fe>Heather Nauert: US is in Syria to defeat ISIS</a></h4><p data-v-275a95fe>U.S. warns more airstrikes on Syria are possible. On 'America's Newsroom,' State Department spokeswoman says the U.S. has seen a series of Russian lies at the United Nations.</p></div></div></div></div><p class="speakable">President Trump has offered State Department spokesperson Heather Nauert the role of U.S. ambassador to the United Nations, a senior administration official told Fox News.</p><div class="ad-container tablet"><div data-ad-pos="tablet" data-ad-size="300x250" data-ad-lz="" class="ad gpt ad-h-250"></div><!----></div><div class="ad-container mobile"><div data-ad-pos="mobile" data-ad-size="300x250" data-ad-lz="" class="ad gpt ad-h-250"></div><!----></div><p class="speakable">It is not clear yet is whether she has accepted the offer to replace the outgoing Nikki Haley as ambassador.</p><div data-ad-pos="inread" data-ad-size="1x1" class="ad gpt ad-h-1"></div><p>The White House would only say Thursday that Nauert&#xA0;&#x201C;is under strong consideration.&quot;</p><p>Nauert met with Trump in the Oval Office on Monday. Several other officials have been named as potential candidates, including U.S. Ambassador to France Jamie McCourt.</p><p>Haley, the former governor of South Carolina, announced earlier this month she would leave the post by the end of this year.</p><div class="ad-container mobile"><div data-ad-pos="mobile" data-ad-size="300x251" data-ad-lz="" class="ad gpt ad-h-250"></div><!----></div><p>Nauert, a former Fox News journalist, was named State Department spokesperson in April 2017, working under both Secretaries of State Rex Tillerson and Mike Pompeo.</p><p>Earlier this year, she also was named acting undersecretary for public diplomacy and public affairs after the dismissal of Steve Goldstein from that post.</p><p><em>Fox News&#x2019; Samuel Chamberlain contributed to this report.</em></p><!----></div><div class="article-meta"><div class="author-bio">John Roberts currently serves as the chief White House correspondent for FOX News Channel (FNC). He joined the network as a senior national correspondent in January 2011, based in the Atlanta bureau.<br>
